 can also define custom blocks. Custom blocks have a title, description, and body. The body of the block can be as long as necessary, and can contain content supported by any available <a href=\"@input-format\">input format</a>.','6.38'),(51,'modules/block/block.module:72','default',_binary 'When working with blocks, remember that:','6.38'),(52,'modules/block/block.module:73','default',_binary 'since not all themes implement the same regions, or display regions in the same way, blocks are positioned on a per-theme basis.','6.38'),(53,'modules/block/block.module:74','default',_binary 'disabled blocks, or blocks not in a region, are never shown.','6.38'),(54,'modules/block/block.module:75','default',_binary 'when throttle module is enabled, throttled blocks (blocks with the <em>Throttle</em> checkbox selected) are hidden during high server loads.','6.38'),(55,'modules/block/block.module:76','default',_binary 'blocks can be configured to be visible only on certain pages.','6.38'),(56,'modules/block/block.module:77','default',_binary 'blocks can be configured to be visible only when specific conditions are true.','6.38'),(57,'modules/block/block.module:78','default',_binary 'blocks can be configured to be visible only for certain user roles.','6.38'),(58,'modules/block/block.module:79','default',_binary 'when allowed by an administrator, specific blocks may be enabled or disabled on a per-user basis using the <em>My account</em> page.','6.38'),(59,'modules/block/block.module:80','default',_binary 'some dynamic blocks, such as those generated by modules, will be displayed only on certain pages.','6.38'),(60,'modules/block/block.module:81','default',_binary 'For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@block\">Block module</a>.','6.38'),(61,'modules/block/block.module:85','default',_binary 'This page provides a drag-and-drop interface for assigning a block to a region, and for controlling the order of blocks within regions. To change the region or order of a block, grab a drag-and-drop handle under the <em>Block</em> column and drag the block to a new location in the list. (Grab a handle by clicking and holding the mouse while hovering over a handle icon.) Since not all themes implement the same regions, or display regions in the same way, blocks are positioned on a per-theme basis. Remember that your changes will not be saved until you click the <em>Save blocks</em> button at the bottom of the page.','6.38'),(62,'modules/block/block.module:87','default',_binary 'To reduce CPU usage, database traffic or bandwidth, blocks may be automatically disabled during high server loads by selecting their <em>Throttle</em> checkbox. Adjust throttle thresholds on the <a href=\"@throttleconfig\">throttle configuration page</a>.','none'),(63,'modules/block/block.module:89','default',_binary 'Click the <em>configure</em> link next to each block to configure its specific title and visibility settings. Use the <a href=\"@add-block\">add block page</a> to create a custom block.','6.38'),(64,'modules/block/block.module:92','default',_binary 'Use this page to create a new custom block. New blocks are disabled by default, and must be moved to a region on the <a href=\"@blocks\">blocks administration page</a> to be visible.','6.38'),(65,'modules/block/block.module:133','default',_binary 'JavaScript List Form','6.38'),(66,'modules/block/block.js:0; modules/block/block.js','default',_binary 'The changes to these blocks will not be saved until the <em>Save blocks</em> button is clicked.','none'),(67,'modules/block/block.module:276','default',_binary 'The block %info was assigned to the invalid region %region and has been disabled.','6.38'),(68,'modules/color/color.module:43','default',_binary 'Color scheme','none'),(69,'modules/color/color.module:171','default',_binary 'Custom','6.38'),(70,'modules/color/color.module:174','default',_binary 'Color set','none'),(71,'modules/color/color.module:182','default',_binary 'Base color','none'),(7