time. This is useful for site administrators who want a quick overview of activities on their site. The logs also record the sequence of events, so it can be useful for debugging site errors.','6.38'),(208,'modules/dblog/dblog.module:22','default',_binary 'The dblog log is simply a list of recorded events containing usage data, performance data, errors, warnings and operational information. Administrators should check the dblog report on a regular basis to ensure their site is working properly.','6.38'),(209,'modules/dblog/dblog.module:23','default',_binary 'For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@dblog\">Dblog module</a>.','6.38'),(210,'modules/dblog/dblog.module:26','default',_binary 'The dblog module monitors your website, capturing system events in a log to be reviewed by an authorized individual at a later time. The dblog log is simply a list of recorded events containing usage data, performance data, errors, warnings and operational information. It is vital to check the dblog report on a regular basis as it is often the only way to tell what is going on.','6.38'),(211,'modules/dblog/dblog.module:47','default',_binary 'Settings for logging to the Drupal database logs. This is the most common method for small to medium sites on shared hosting. The logs are viewable from the admin pages.','6.38'),(212,'modules/filter/filter.module:35','default',_binary 'If you cannot find the settings for a certain filter, make sure you have enabled it on the <a href=\"@url\">view tab</a> first.','none'),(213,'modules/filter/filter.module:71','default',_binary 'Input formats','6.38'),(214,'modules/filter/filter.module:91','default',_binary 'Delete input format','6.38'),(215,'modules/filter/filter.module:99','default',_binary 'Compose tips','6.38'),(216,'modules/filter/filter.module:131','default',_binary 'Rearrange','6.38'),(217,'modules/filter/filter.module:182,180','default',_binary 'Allowed HTML tags: @tags','6.38'),(218,'modules/filter/filter.module