s to try and remove duplicates from a view, though it does not always work. Note that this can slow queries down, so use it with caution.','6.38'),(2968,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/views/ajax/display/latest_links/block_1/exposed_block','default',_binary 'Put the exposed form in a block','6.38'),(2969,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/views/ajax/display/latest_links/block_1/exposed_block','default',_binary 'If set, any exposed widgets will not appear with this view. Instead, a block will be made available to the Drupal block administration system, and the exposed form will appear there. Note that this block must be enabled manually, Views will not enable it for you.','6.38'),(2970,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/views/ajax/add-item/latest_links/default/filter','default',_binary 'Node type','6.38'),(2971,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/views/ajax/analyze/latest_links','default',_binary 'Display %display has no access control but does not contain a filter for published nodes.','6.38'),(2972,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/block','default',_binary 'Exposed form: @view-@display_id','6.38'),(2973,'/drupal-6.38/admin/build/block/configure/block/1','default',_binary 'blocco \'<em>Lore Ipsum</em>\'','6.38'),(2974,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'This module helps in site development.  Specifically, when an access control module is used to limit access to some or all nodes, this module provides some feedback showing the node_access table in the database.','6.38'),(2975,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The node_access table is one method Drupal provides to hide content from some users while displaying it to others.  By default, Drupal shows all nodes to all users.  There are a number of optional modules which may be installed to hide content from some users.','6.38'),(2976,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'If you have not installed any of these modules, you really have no need for the devel_node_access module.  This module is intended for use during development, so that developers and admins can confirm that the node_access table is working as expected.  You probably do not want this module enabled on a production site.','6.38'),(2977,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'This module provides two blocks.  One called Devel Node Access by User is visible when a single node is shown on a page.  This block shows which users can view, update or delete the node shown.  Note that this block uses an inefficient algorithm to produce its output.  You should only enable this block on sites with very few user accounts.','6.38'),(2978,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The second block provided by this module shows the entries in the node_access table for any nodes shown on the current page.  You can enable the debug mode on the <a href=\"@settings_page\">settings page</a> to display much more information, but this can cause considerable overhead.  Because the tables shown are wide, it is recommended to enable the blocks in the page footer rather than a sidebar.','6.38'),(2979,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'This module also provides a <a href=\"@summary_page\">summary page</a> which shows general information about your node_access table.  If you have installed the Views module, you may browse node_access by realm.','6.38'),(2980,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The Image module is used to create and administer images for your site. Each image is stored as a post, with thumbnails of the original generated automatically. There are two default derivative image sizes, \"thumbnail\" and \"preview\". The \"thumbnail\" size is shown as preview image in posts and when browsing image galleries. The \"preview\" size is the default size when viewing an image node page.','6.38'),(2981,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The settings page for Image module allows the image directory and the image sizes to be configured.','6.38'),(2982,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'Image module ships with contributed modules. Their settings can be accessed from the image settings page.','6.38'),(2983,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'Image attach is used to add an existing or new image to a node. The selected image will show up in a predefined spot on the selected node.','6.38'),(2984,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'Image gallery is used to organize and display images in galleries. The list tab allows users to edit existing image gallery names, descriptions, parents and relative position, known as a weight. The add galleries tab allows you to create a new image gallery defining name, description, parent and weight. If the <a href=\"@views-url\">Views module</a> is installed, then the Image gallery module settings are mostly replaced by settings of the view.','6.38'),(2985,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'Image import is used to import batches of images. The administration page lets you define the folder from which images will be imported.','6.38'),(2986,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The separate <a href=\"@img-assist-url\">Image assist module</a> can be installed to upload and insert images into posts.','6.38'),(2987,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'You can:','6.38'),(2988,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'Configure image sizes and file directories at <a href=\"@image-settings-url\">Administer &raquo; Site configuration &raquo; Image</a>.','6.38'),(2989,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@image-url\">Image module</a>.','6.38'),(2990,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'The Image gallery module allows you to organize your image nodes into galleries. Images are placed into galleries in the same way as nodes are given taxonomy terms.','6.38'),(2991,'/drupal-6.38/admin/by-module','default',_binary 'View your <a href=\"@image-gallery-ur