binary 'Actions available to Drupal:','6.38'),(3040,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions','default',_binary 'Make a new advanced action available','6.38'),(3041,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions','default',_binary 'Create','6.38'),(3042,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions','default',_binary 'Actions are individual tasks that the system can do, such as unpublishing a piece of content or banning a user. Modules, such as the trigger module, can fire these actions when certain system events happen; for example, when a new post is added or when a user logs in. Modules may also provide additional actions.','6.38'),(3043,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions','default',_binary 'There are two types of actions: simple and advanced. Simple actions do not require any additional configuration, and are listed here automatically. Advanced actions can do more than simple actions; for example, send an e-mail to a specified address, or check for certain words within a piece of content. These actions need to be created and configured first before they may be used. To create an advanced action, select the action from the drop-down below and click the <em>Create</em> button.','6.38'),(3044,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'A unique description for this advanced action. This description will be displayed in the interface of modules that integrate with actions, such as Trigger module.','6.38'),(3045,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'Recipient','6.38'),(3046,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'The email address to which the message should be sent OR enter %author if you would like to send an e-mail to the author of the original post.','6.38'),(3047,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'The subject of the message.','6.38'),(3048,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'The message that should be sent. You may include the following variables: %site_name, %username, %node_url, %node_type, %title, %teaser, %body, %term_name, %term_description, %term_id, %vocabulary_name, %vocabulary_description, %vocabulary_id. Not all variables will be available in all contexts.','6.38'),(3049,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/actions/configure/daa75f478e3093ab107e657da6620a91','default',_binary 'An advanced action offers additional configuration options which may be filled out below. Changing the <em>Description</em> field is recommended, in order to better identify the precise action taking place. This description will be displayed in modules such as the trigger module when assigning actions to system events, so it is best if it is as descriptive as possible (for example, \"Send e-mail to Moderation Team\" rather than simply \"Send e-mail\").','6.38'),(3050,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/coder','default',_binary 'After setting these defaults, use <a href=\"@url\">coder</a> to perform code reviews.','6.38'),(3051,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Query log','6.38'),(3052,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Collect query info. If disabled, no query log functionality will work.','6.38'),(3053,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Collect query info','6.38'),(3054,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Display query log','6.38'),(3055,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Display a log of the database queries needed to generate the current page, and the execution time for each. Also, queries which are repeated during a single page view are summed in the # column, and printed in red since they are candidates for caching.','6.38'),(3056,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'Sort query log','6.38'),(3057,'/drupal-6.38/admin/settings/devel','default',_binary 'by 